{{wiktionary|polyclinic}}
A '''polyclinic''' is a [[clinic]] that provides both general and specialist examinations and treatments to [[outpatient]]s and is usually independent of a hospital. The term is not clearly defined and includes:

* [[Polyclinics in England]], large health care centres able to provide a wider range of services than a standard doctor's (GP) office, an initiative of [[Ara Darzi|Ara Darzi, Baron Darzi of Denham]] in 2007.
* [[The Polyclinic]], in Seattle, Washington, US

==See also==
* [[Outpatient clinic (hospital department)|Outpatient department of a hospital]] (rarely called ''policlinic'' in American English, and only when referring to European hospital outpatient departments)
* [[District general hospital|General hospital]]; when a polyclinic is so large that it is in fact a hospital, it is also called a general hospital.<ref>[http://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/polyclinic polyclinic] in Collins English Dictionary</ref>
*{{in title|Polyclinic}}
*{{in title|Outpatient}}

