'''WellChoice, Incorporated''' is the parent company of Empire [[Blue Cross Blue Shield Association|Blue Cross-Blue Shield]] of [[New York (state)|New York]], created when Empire became a [[stock market|publicly traded]] company in 2003. WellChoice is listed on the [[Fortune 500]] with revenues of over [[United States dollar|US$]]5,000,000,000.

==History==
Empire changed the named of its parent company to WellChoice in November 2002 after its initial public offering.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Dateline: New York|journal=''[[Modern Healthcare]]''|date=27 June 2005|volume=35|series=Regional News|issue=26|pages=28}}</ref>

In late 2005 it was announced that Wellchoice would begin a merger with [[WellPoint Health Networks Incorporated|WellPoint]], also a Fortune 500 company, in January 2006.

